<paragraph blockId="50.[159,1116,915,1321]" pageId="50" pageNumber="3007">
<emphasis box="[199,297,979,1003]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="3007">Ecology.</emphasis>
Intertidal, about spring low tide level, wrapped around coral boulders. Also found drifting in the lagoon in huge quantities, locally forming a floating mass of 0.5 m thick.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="50.[159,1116,915,1321]" box="[199,963,1074,1098]" pageId="50" pageNumber="3007">
<emphasis box="[199,341,1074,1098]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="3007">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[353,425,1074,1098]" name="China" pageId="50" pageNumber="3007">China</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[440,554,1074,1098]" name="Indonesia" pageId="50" pageNumber="3007">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
, Rodrigues (this paper), 
<collectingCountry box="[849,959,1074,1098]" name="Tanzania" pageId="50" pageNumber="3007">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="50.[159,1116,915,1321]" pageId="50" pageNumber="3007">
<emphasis box="[199,271,1106,1130]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="3007">Notes.</emphasis>
(1) See note for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Howe" authorityYear="1920" baseAuthorityName="C. Agardh" box="[481,631,1106,1130]" class="Phaeophyceae" family="Scytosiphonaceae" genus="Hydroclathrus" kingdom="Chromista" order="Scytosiphonales" pageId="50" pageNumber="3007" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="clathratus">
<emphasis box="[481,631,1106,1130]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="3007">H. clathratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. (2) According to 
<bibRefCitation author="TSENG, C. K." box="[856,1064,1106,1130]" pageId="50" pageNumber="3007" refId="ref37927" refString="TSENG, C. K., 1984, Common Seaweeds of China (Beijing: Science Press), 316 pp." type="book" year="1984">Tseng (1984: 186)</bibRefCitation>
this species is endemic to 
<collectingCountry box="[428,501,1138,1162]" name="China" pageId="50" pageNumber="3007">China</collectingCountry>
. Since then it has been reported from one site in 
<collectingCountry box="[159,270,1170,1194]" name="Indonesia" pageId="50" pageNumber="3007">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="VERHEIJ, E. &amp; PRUD'HOMME VAN REINE, W. F." box="[290,852,1170,1194]" pageId="50" pageNumber="3007" pagination="385 - 510" refId="ref38302" refString="VERHEIJ, E. and PRUD'HOMME VAN REINE, W. F., 1993, Seaweeds of the Spermonde Archipelago, SW Sulawesi, Indonesia, Blumea, 37, 385 - 510." type="journal article" year="1993">Verheij and Prud’homme van Reine, 1993: 435</bibRefCitation>
), from the 
<collectingCountry box="[990,1115,1170,1194]" name="Philippines" pageId="50" pageNumber="3007">Philippines</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="TRONO, C. G., JR" box="[167,379,1201,1225]" pageId="50" pageNumber="3007" refId="ref37894" refString="TRONO, C. G., JR, 1997 Field Guide and Atlas of the Seaweed Resources of the Philippines (Makati City, Philippines: Bookmark), 306 pp." type="book" year="1997">Trono, 1997: 123</bibRefCitation>
) and from several locations in 
<collectingCountry box="[779,885,1201,1225]" name="Tanzania" pageId="50" pageNumber="3007">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="COPPEJANS, E. &amp; LELIAERT, F. &amp; DE CLERCK, O." pageId="50" pageNumber="3007" pagination="31 - 93" refId="ref32983" refString="COPPEJANS, E., LELIAERT, F. and DE CLERCK, O., 2000, Annotated list of new records of marine macroalgae for Kenya and Tanzania since Isaac's and Jaasund's publications, Biologisch Jaarboek Dodonaea, 67, 31 - 93." type="journal article" year="2000">
Coppejans 
<emphasis box="[1045,1101,1202,1226]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="3007">et al</emphasis>
., 2000: 60
</bibRefCitation>
). (3) When decaying, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tseng and Lu" authorityYear="1983" box="[544,653,1234,1258]" class="Phaeophyceae" family="Scytosiphonaceae" genus="Hydroclathrus" kingdom="Chromista" order="Scytosiphonales" pageId="50" pageNumber="3007" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="tenuis">
<emphasis box="[544,653,1234,1258]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="3007">H. tenuis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
turns green. As a result it has been identified as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Forsskal" authorityYear="1775" box="[310,479,1265,1289]" class="Ulvophyceae" family="Ulvaceae" genus="Ulva" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ulvales" pageId="50" pageNumber="3007" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="species" species="reticulata">
<emphasis box="[310,479,1265,1289]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="3007">Ulva reticulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in previous ecological studies of Rodrigues, based on the morphological resemblance.
</paragraph>
